The '''Darkshear''', also known as the '''spear of midnight black''', was an arcane [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] [[Force power/Legends|Force power]]. It enabled a [[The Force/Legends|Force]]-user to channel the Dark in a sustained, directed burst. It could be used to forge an imperceivable melee weapon in the form of a piercing metaphysical spear of midnight black.<ref name="Imperial">{{SW|url=news/the-imperial-warlords-despoilers-of-an-empire-part-3|series=The Imperial Warlords: Despoilers of an Empire|text=Part 3|nolive=1}}</ref> A Darkshear strike caused victims to suffer the cumulative damage of years of atrophy in a single moment. Armor rusts and becomes brittle, [[Power cell/Legends|power cells]] drain, and machinery jams. Individuals can age thirty years in an instant, with vital body parts such as their heart, lungs, and joints failing in the midst of battle. Darkshear damage could sometimes be reversed with [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]], but might require [[Cybernetics/Legends|prosthetic]] replacement.<ref name="The Unknown Regions">''[[The Unknown Regions]]''</ref>  

The [[Sorcerers of Rhand]]'s unique [[Way of the Dark|perspective]] on the Force gave them access to many inordinate capabilities, such as Darkshear. They became masters of this arcane technique and used it in the rare event they were threatened with face-to-face confrontation.<ref name="The Unknown Regions" />

==Behind the scenes==
While this technique is not available in the computer game ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Dark Forces II]]'', it is described in the novel ''[[Dark Forces: Jedi Knight]]'' as the method that Katarn uses to kill Boc. However, in the game, Boc is killed simply by the lightsaber duel.

